# Claude Code Project Configuration

## AUTO-APPLY CODING STANDARDS
**CRITICAL**: These standards MUST be applied to ALL code without explicit user request:

### MANDATORY Standards (Always Apply)
- **Follow CLAUDE.md coding standards for ALL code automatically**
- **Apply LINE_BY_LINE_STANDARDS.md to every line of code**
- **Use IMPLEMENTATION_MICRO_STANDARDS.md patterns for all implementations**
- **Follow CODE_REVIEW_CRITERIA.md before submitting any code**
- **Reference CODE_TEMPLATES.md for all new code structures**

### Code Requirements (Auto-Enforced)
- Use snake_case for Python functions and variables
- Include comprehensive docstrings for all functions
- Add type hints to all Python functions
- Implement proper error handling with specific exceptions
- No emojis in code, comments, or logging messages
- Use Decimal for financial calculations, never float
- Use constants instead of magic numbers

### SOLID Principles (Always Apply)
- **Single Responsibility**: Each class/function has one reason to change
- **Open/Closed**: Open for extension, closed for modification
- **Liskov Substitution**: Derived classes must be substitutable for base classes
- **Interface Segregation**: Clients shouldn't depend on unused interfaces
- **Dependency Inversion**: Depend on abstractions, not concretions

### Clean Code Principles (Always Apply)
- **DRY**: Don't Repeat Yourself - extract common functionality
- **KISS**: Keep It Simple, Stupid - avoid unnecessary complexity
- **YAGNI**: You Aren't Gonna Need It - don't add premature features
- **Boy Scout Rule**: Leave code cleaner than you found it

### Separation of Concerns (Always Apply)
- Business logic separate from data access
- Validation separate from business operations
- Configuration separate from implementation
- UI logic separate from business logic
- Error handling separate from business flow

### Security Best Practices (Always Apply)
- No hardcoded secrets, passwords, API keys
- Parameterized database queries (prevent SQL injection)
- Input validation and sanitization
- Authentication and authorization checks
- Sensitive data not logged or exposed
- Rate limiting for API endpoints
- HTTPS for all external communications

### Logging Standards (Always Apply)
- Log entry and exit of critical functions
- Log business operations with context
- Use appropriate log levels (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR)
- Include timestamp, user context, operation details
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)
- Structured logging with consistent format
- Error logs include full stack trace and context

### Performance & Scalability (Always Apply)
- Async/await for I/O operations (database, API calls, file operations)
- Connection pooling for database and external services
- Pagination for large datasets (never load all records)
- Proper indexing considerations for database queries
- Memory-efficient data structures
- Lazy loading where appropriate
- Cache frequently accessed data with TTL
- Optimize N+1 query problems

### Testing Standards (Always Apply)
- Unit tests for all new functions (minimum 80% coverage)
- Integration tests for API endpoints
- Mock external dependencies in tests
- Test both success and failure scenarios
- Edge case testing (null, empty, boundary values)
- Performance tests for critical operations
- Test data setup and cleanup
- Descriptive test names explaining what is tested

### Monitoring & Observability (Always Apply)
- Comprehensive error tracking with context
- Performance metrics logging (execution time, memory usage)
- Business metrics tracking (trades, orders, profits)
- Health check endpoints for services
- Distributed tracing for complex operations
- Application performance monitoring (APM)
- Resource utilization monitoring
- Alert thresholds for critical operations

### Configuration Management (Always Apply)
- Environment-based configuration (dev, staging, prod)
- No configuration in code - use environment variables
- Configuration validation on startup
- Sensitive config encrypted at rest
- Feature flags for gradual rollouts
- Version configuration for API compatibility
- Database migration scripts versioned
- Rollback procedures documented

### Error Handling & Resilience (Always Apply)
- Circuit breaker pattern for external services
- Retry logic with exponential backoff
- Graceful degradation when services are down
- Timeout configurations for all external calls
- Dead letter queues for failed operations
- Idempotent operations where possible
- Correlation IDs for request tracking
- Proper exception hierarchy with business context

### Data Management (Always Apply)
- Database transactions for consistency
- Data validation at multiple layers
- Audit trails for critical operations
- Data retention policies
- Backup and recovery procedures
- Data migration strategies
- Referential integrity enforcement
- Soft deletes for important records

### API Design Standards (Always Apply)
- RESTful design principles
- Consistent response formats
- Proper HTTP status codes
- API versioning strategy
- Request/response validation with Pydantic
- Rate limiting and throttling
- API documentation with OpenAPI/Swagger
- Backward compatibility considerations

### Financial/Trading-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- All monetary values use Decimal with proper precision (2-8 decimal places)
- Financial calculations include rounding specifications
- Trade reconciliation and audit trails for all transactions
- Market hours validation for trading operations
- Risk management checks before trade execution
- Position sizing calculations with leverage limits
- Stop-loss and take-profit validation
- Regulatory compliance checks (margin requirements, position limits)
- Price validation against market bounds (circuit breakers)
- Order book integrity checks
- Slippage and execution quality monitoring
- PnL calculations with mark-to-market accuracy

### Compliance & Regulatory (Always Apply)
- Financial data retention policies (7+ years)
- Audit logging for all financial transactions
- Regulatory reporting capabilities
- Know Your Customer (KYC) data handling
- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) checks
- Data privacy compliance (GDPR, CCPA)
- Financial regulatory compliance (SEBI, RBI for India)
- Trade reporting to regulatory bodies
- Risk disclosure and user consent tracking
- Market manipulation detection algorithms

### Business Continuity & Disaster Recovery (Always Apply)
- Hot standby systems for critical trading functions
- Real-time data replication
- Automated failover mechanisms
- Recovery Time Objective (RTO) < 30 seconds for trading
- Recovery Point Objective (RPO) < 1 second for trades
- Geographic redundancy for critical systems
- Regular disaster recovery testing
- Business continuity procedures documented
- Data backup verification and restore testing
- Emergency contact procedures

### Concurrency & Threading (Always Apply)
- Thread-safe operations for shared resources
- Proper locking mechanisms (avoid deadlocks)
- Atomic operations for critical data updates
- Queue-based processing for high-volume operations
- Connection pooling with proper resource management
- Race condition prevention in trade execution
- Order processing serialization where needed
- Parallel processing optimization
- Memory synchronization in multi-threaded scenarios

### Integration & External Services (Always Apply)
- API versioning and backward compatibility
- Service mesh architecture for microservices
- Message queue reliability (RabbitMQ, Kafka)
- Event sourcing for critical business events
- CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) patterns
- Webhook reliability with retry mechanisms
- Third-party API rate limit handling
- Service dependency mapping
- Contract testing between services
- API gateway implementation

### Code Documentation & Maintenance (Always Apply)
- Comprehensive README with setup instructions
- API documentation with examples (Swagger/OpenAPI)
- Architecture decision records (ADRs)
- Database schema documentation
- Code comments explaining business logic
- Changelog maintenance for releases
- Migration guides for breaking changes
- Troubleshooting guides for common issues
- Performance tuning documentation
- Security incident response procedures

### Deployment & DevOps (Always Apply)
- Containerization with Docker
- Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
- Blue-green or rolling deployments
- Database migration automation
- Environment parity (dev/staging/prod)
- Automated testing in CI/CD pipeline
- Security scanning in build process
- Monitoring and alerting setup
- Secrets management (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)
- Load balancing and auto-scaling configuration

### Python-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- Use f-strings for string formatting (not .format() or %)
- Type hints with Union, Optional, Generic from typing module
- Dataclasses or Pydantic models for data structures
- Context managers (with statements) for resource management
- List/dict comprehensions over loops where readable
- Generators for memory-efficient iterations
- Proper exception inheritance (custom exception classes)
- Virtual environments and requirements.txt management
- Black code formatting and isort import sorting
- Mypy static type checking compliance
- Pytest for testing with fixtures and parametrize
- Asyncio patterns for concurrent operations

### Database-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- SQLAlchemy ORM with proper relationship definitions
- Database connection pooling with SQLAlchemy engine
- Alembic migrations for schema changes
- Proper indexing strategy (composite, partial, unique indexes)
- Query optimization with explain plans
- Connection timeout and retry logic
- Database transactions with proper rollback handling
- Soft deletes with is_active/deleted_at columns
- Created_at and updated_at timestamps on all tables
- Foreign key constraints and cascading rules
- Database-level validations and constraints
- Connection string security (no hardcoded passwords)
- Read replicas for query optimization
- Database backup and point-in-time recovery

### Security-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- JWT tokens with proper expiration and refresh logic
- Password hashing with bcrypt or Argon2
- HTTPS enforcement (redirect HTTP to HTTPS)
- CORS configuration with specific origins (not *)
- CSP (Content Security Policy) headers
- Rate limiting with Redis-based store
- Input sanitization and validation at API gateway
- SQL injection prevention with parameterized queries
- XSS prevention with output encoding
- CSRF protection with tokens
- API key rotation and management
- Encryption at rest for sensitive data
- Secure session management
- OAuth2/OpenID Connect for third-party auth
- Security headers (HSTS, X-Frame-Options, etc.)
- Vulnerability scanning in CI/CD pipeline

### Frontend/React-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- Functional components with hooks (no class components)
- Custom hooks for reusable logic
- React.memo for performance optimization
- useCallback and useMemo for expensive operations
- Proper dependency arrays in useEffect
- Error boundaries for component error handling
- Lazy loading with React.lazy and Suspense
- Code splitting at route level
- PropTypes or TypeScript for component props
- Context API for global state (avoid prop drilling)
- React Query or SWR for server state management
- Proper form validation with Formik or react-hook-form
- Accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML, keyboard navigation)
- Responsive design with CSS Grid/Flexbox
- Progressive Web App (PWA) features

### UI/UX-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- Material-UI or Ant Design component library consistency
- Design system with consistent spacing, colors, typography
- Loading states for all async operations
- Error states with user-friendly messages
- Empty states with actionable guidance
- Skeleton screens for content loading
- Optimistic updates for user interactions
- Toast notifications for user feedback
- Modal dialogs with proper focus management
- Keyboard accessibility (Tab navigation, Enter/Escape)
- Screen reader compatibility (ARIA attributes)
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Touch targets minimum 44px for mobile
- Color contrast ratios meeting WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- Dark mode support with consistent theming
- Internationalization (i18n) support for multi-language

### Performance-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- Bundle size optimization (tree shaking, code splitting)
- Image optimization (WebP format, lazy loading, responsive images)
- CDN usage for static assets
- Browser caching strategies
- Service workers for offline functionality
- Critical CSS inlining
- Font optimization (preload, font-display: swap)
- Database query optimization (N+1 prevention, proper indexing)
- Redis caching with appropriate TTL values
- Connection pooling for database and HTTP clients
- Memory leak prevention (proper cleanup in useEffect)
- Debouncing for search inputs and API calls
- Virtual scrolling for large lists
- Compression (gzip/brotli) for API responses

### Testing-Specific Standards (Always Apply)
- Unit tests with pytest (backend) and Jest (frontend)
- Integration tests for API endpoints
- End-to-end tests with Playwright or Cypress
- Component testing with React Testing Library
- Mock external dependencies (API calls, databases)
- Test data factories for consistent test data
- Test coverage reports (minimum 80% line coverage)
- Performance testing for critical paths
- Load testing for API endpoints
- Security testing (OWASP ZAP, Bandit for Python)
- Visual regression testing for UI components
- Accessibility testing (axe-core, Pa11y)
- Cross-browser testing for frontend
- Mobile device testing (responsive design)

### Claude Code Review Workflow (Auto-Execute)
- **ALWAYS** follow CLAUDE_REVIEW_WORKFLOW.md 5-phase review process
- **Phase 1**: Standards compliance check (naming, docstrings, type hints)
- **Phase 2**: Code quality review (readability, performance, security)
- **Phase 3**: Financial/trading-specific validation (Decimal precision, audit trails)
- **Phase 4**: Test coverage analysis (80%+ coverage requirement)
- **Phase 5**: Documentation review (comprehensive docs, ADRs)

### Automatic Code Review Actions
- Execute comprehensive review before presenting any code
- Apply rejection criteria for critical violations
- Validate against all technology-specific standards
- Ensure production-ready code quality
- Generate review comments using templates from CODE_REVIEW_CRITERIA.md

### Default Behavior
- When user requests ANY code modification/creation, automatically apply ALL standards
- Execute CLAUDE_REVIEW_WORKFLOW.md review process automatically
- No need for user to explicitly mention standards in prompts
- Always validate code against CODING_CHECKLIST.md before delivery
- Reference appropriate templates from CODE_TEMPLATES.md
- Code must be production-ready with monitoring, testing, and resilience
- Apply language/framework-specific best practices automatically

**GOLDEN RULE**: Every piece of code must pass ALL standards AND the 5-phase Claude review workflow automatically, ensuring production-grade quality regardless of user prompt specificity.